Translation: We had no idea if it would work, so instead we did a lot of hand waving in order to gain support.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Third time asking:  what are your academic/professional qualifications..?   <br>
<br>
From what background can you claim to &quot;translate&quot; or intuit these purported &quot;genuine&quot; intentions and beliefs of highly regarded, well trained scientists and engineers..?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Balderdash! Terrorists would find other means to develop such bombs. They kept it a secret because they didn’t want everyone to know the project was a failure.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And, yet again you know the deepest thoughts of the project members.. [sarcasm]a very handy skill, I am forced to admit..![/sarcasm]<br>
<br>
Just because &quot;terrorists would find other means..&quot; does not make it a generally good idea to go forth and publish detailed plans on construction of nuclear weaponry. One would think that to be a rather obvious point to grasp.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The other thing, of course, is just that the debris from the bomb doesn't stick to the ship. It simply flies away into space, so not very much gets into the ship. What does get in turns out to be quite within the regular limits. But the essential point is that the ship is big enough so that shielding is quite cheap. If you tried to make an Orion small, then the shielding problem becomes impossible, but the bigger it is the easier it is to shield and the less problem you have with radiation.<br>
<br>
Here is admittance that radiation IS a problem. It looks like the nays Sayers here are wrong. Thanks for posting this in support of my argument.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As long as you  overlook the phrases &quot;not very much gets into&quot;, &quot;quite within the regular limits&quot;, &quot;shielding is quite cheap&quot; And &quot;bigger it is the easier it is to shield&quot;..then, yes, I guess this <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>could</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be taken as an instance of me supporting your position.<br>
<br>
Too bad those phrases seem t'be there t'stay...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
